(11, 1, '2012-04-22 12:01:13', '2012-04-22 04:01:13', '<strong>Norida Zainol</strong> has vast corporate experience in Human Resource Management fields with her last appointment in the corporate world being the Human Resource Development Manager of an internationally recognized corporation. She provides human resource development services, implements and conducts programmes to internal companies within the group. A strong advocate of Human Talents Development specializing in the conceptualization, design, development and delivery of training on organization development, competency development, strategic planning and identification of human potential.\r\n\r\nShe entered the profession in 1980 and has engaged in the full spectrum of human resource management including measurement service for employee selections, developing career development and succession planning systems, performance management and evaluation systems, compensation and remuneration packages and managing human capital in a downsized organization.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.theswitch.com.my/files/pot01.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<strong>Lim Teck Hoe</strong> is an internationally known speaker in the field of learning, memory, thinking and creativity. He has trained and helped more than 10,000 people ranging from students, housewives, working adults, executives, government officials and senior citizens throughout South East Asia. With more than 4 years of experience, he is one of the pioneers and leaders of this field in Asia. He has achieved more than 88% satisfactory rating in all his training.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHe won the silver medal in Names &amp; Faces event in World Memory Championships 2002 and is currently the Asia Memory Record Holder. He is also the coach of World Junior Memory Record Holder, Asia Female Memory Record Holder and numerous Grandmasters of Memory. He works very closely with the world renowned Mr. Tony Buzan and many other top thinkers in the world.\r\n\r\nHe is a strong advocate and believer of Mental Development. He has organized many activities to create the platform for mental development. He is the Organizing Chairman of the World Memory Championships 2003, Founder of Asia Memory Championships, Malaysia Mind Sports Council, Malaysia Memory Championships and Malaysia Brain Games, which includes Memory Skills, Creativity Thinking, Speed Reading &amp; Intelligence competitions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.theswitch.com.my/files/pot02.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<strong>Tengku Faizwa Tengku Razif</strong> is one of the pioneer Malay trainers specializing in brain, learning, memory and thinking. She has been practicing in this field since graduating from Universiti Sains Malaysia with Bachelor of Management (Hons) in year 2001. She is a strong believer in enhancing human potential through the correct usage of our brain.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShe has helped many students in realizing their potential. The most notable achievement was one of her students managed to win the Bronze medal in World Memory Championships 2003 and eventually became the Malaysia Memory Champion. Many of her students also achieved the Grandmaster of Memory norm in World Memory Championships.\r\n\r\nShe is the co-organizer of World Memory Championships 2003 and co-founder of Asia Memory Championships, Malaysia Mind Sports Council, Malaysia Memory Championships and Malaysia Brain Games.', 'The Partners', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-partners', '', '', '2012-04-22 12:20:02', '2012-04-22 04:20:02', '', 6, 'http://localhost/ideaspark/?page_id=11', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(12, 1, '2012-04-22 12:01:11', '2012-04-22 04:01:11', '<strong>Norida Zainol</strong> has vast corporate experience in Human Resource Management fields with her last appointment in the corporate world being the Human Resource Development Manager of an internationally recognized corporation. She provides human resource development services, implements and conducts programmes to internal companies within the group. A strong advocate of Human Talents Development specializing in the conceptualization, design, development and delivery of training on organization development, competency development, strategic planning and identification of human potential.\n\nShe entered the profession in 1980 and has engaged in the full spectrum of human resource management including measurement service for employee selections, developing career development and succession planning systems, performance management and evaluation systems, compensation and remuneration packages and managing human capital in a downsized organization.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<hr />\n\n<img src="http://www.theswitch.com.my/files/pot01.jpg" alt="" />\n<strong>Lim Teck Hoe</strong> is an internationally known speaker in the field of learning, memory, thinking and creativity. He has trained and helped more than 10,000 people ranging from students, housewives, working adults, executives, government officials and senior citizens throughout South East Asia. With more than 4 years of experience, he is one of the pioneers and leaders of this field in Asia. He has achieved more than 88% satisfactory rating in all his training.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHe won the silver medal in Names &amp; Faces event in World Memory Championships 2002 and is currently the Asia Memory Record Holder. He is also the coach of World Junior Memory Record Holder, Asia Female Memory Record Holder and numerous Grandmasters of Memory. He works very closely with the world renowned Mr. Tony Buzan and many other top thinkers in the world.\n\nHe is a strong advocate and believer of Mental Development. He has organized many activities to create the platform for mental development. He is the Organizing Chairman of the World Memory Championships 2003, Founder of Asia Memory Championships, Malaysia Mind Sports Council, Malaysia Memory Championships and Malaysia Brain Games, which includes Memory Skills, Creativity Thinking, Speed Reading &amp; Intelligence competitions.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<hr />\n\n<img src="http://www.theswitch.com.my/files/pot02.jpg" alt="" />\n<strong>Tengku Faizwa Tengku Razif</strong> is one of the pioneer Malay trainers specializing in brain, learning, memory and thinking. She has been practicing in this field since graduating from Universiti Sains Malaysia with Bachelor of Management (Hons) in year 2001. She is a strong believer in enhancing human potential through the correct usage of our brain.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nShe has helped many students in realizing their potential. The most notable achievement was one of her students managed to win the Bronze medal in World Memory Championships 2003 and eventually became the Malaysia Memory Champion. Many of her students also achieved the Grandmaster of Memory norm in World Memory Championships.\n\nShe is the co-organizer of World Memory Championships 2003 and co-founder of Asia Memory Championships, Malaysia Mind Sports Council, Malaysia Memory Championships and Malaysia Brain Games.', 'The Partners', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision', '', '', '2012-04-22 12:01:11', '2012-04-22 04:01:11', '', 11, 'http://localhost/ideaspark/?p=12', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(13, 1, '2012-04-22 12:02:52', '2012-04-22 04:02:52', '<img src="http://theswitch.com.my/files/Switch_MapBookCover.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="317" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Mind Mapplications For Students</strong>\r\n<em>Learning Made Fun, Funny &amp; Funky</em>\r\n\r\nThis is about 100 pages book written by Lim Teck Hoe and Tengku Faizwa Tengku Razif. The target readers are students from age 9 to 17. This book is based on their experience of teaching the applications of Mind Map into school curriculum. The idea of this book is to show some real examples taken from school books and Mind Map the text into an interesting and effective manner of Mind Map.\r\n\r\nMind Map was originated by Mr. Tony Buzan in early 1970’s. Mind Map is an effective graphical learning method that synergizes the usage of both left and right hemispheres. It involves the usage of words, numbers, logic, analysis with colours, images, dimension, association and imagination. Mr. Tony Buzan has written many books on Mind Map, however, both Lim Teck Hoe and Tengku Faizwa feel that there should be a book that shows more examples of Mind Map in real applications. This is a book where every page of text will be accompanied with a hand drawn Mind Map.\r\n\r\nThis book can be divided into 4 main areas:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Understanding Our Brain and Traditional Note Making and Note Taking Systems.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Explanation about Brain and the traditional note systems are based on the research of Mr. Tony Buzan, Prof Roger Sperry and also based on the authors’ experience.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	<li>Understanding Mind Maps and How To Mind Map</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The understanding of Mind Maps and How To Mind Map are based on the works of Mr. Tony Buzan as well as the authors’ experience.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	<li>How To Use Mind Map for Brainstorming, Essay Writing, Revisions and Examinations</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The authors wrote this section of the book based on their own experience as well as examples from their students who has benefited themselves using Mind Maps.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	<li>Examples of Mind Map Applications into Language, Mathematics, Science, History and Geography</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The authors used examples taken from related school books and all Mind Maps drawn are based on their own and also their students experience and understanding.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe authors hope that this book will be able to show an effective way on how to tap the ability of our brain. They also hope that this book will encourage the readers especially students to be able to use Mind Maps to make their learning more effective, efficient, fun and funny.', 'Products', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'products', '', '', '2012-04-22 12:20:05', '2012-04-22 04:20:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ideaspark/?page_id=13', 2, 'page', '', 0),
(14, 1, '2012-04-22 12:02:42', '2012-04-22 04:02:42', '', 'Products', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision', '', '', '2012-04-22 12:02:42', '2012-04-22 04:02:42', '', 13, 'http://localhost/ideaspark/?p=14', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(15, 1, '2012-04-22 12:03:09', '2012-04-22 04:03:09', 'Our core services include:\r\n<h3>Education &amp; Training</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>The <em>Switch</em> – Memory Improvement ‘N’ Development (MIND®) Program</strong>\r\n- To unlock the secrets to your Super Memory</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The <em>Switch</em> – Memory Advancing Procedure (MAP®) Program (For Students)</strong>\r\n- Application of Memory Skills in school / university subjects</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The <em>Switch</em> – Make More Money With Memory (M4) Program (For Adults)</strong>\r\n- Use memory skills to coordinate your brain, manage communication skills, success and intelligence</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The <em>Switch</em> – Science and The Art of Reading (STAR®) Program</strong>\r\n- Develop fast and efficient reading power</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The <em>Switch</em> – Innovation &amp; Creativity Thinking Technology (ICTT®) Program</strong>\r\n- Developing skills to provide creativity and innovation</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The <em>Switch</em> – KWIC® Thinking&amp;Learning Tool Program</strong>\r\n- The most powerful note taking and brain storming tool</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Consultation &amp; Facilitation</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Organizational Creativity &amp; Innovation Audit</li>\r\n	<li>Developing Creative &amp; Innovative Workforce &amp; Environment</li>\r\n	<li>Strategic, Business &amp; Innovation Planning Facilitation</li>\r\n	<li>Switch Clique Program - Applying Learning Principles Into Existing Training Programs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Special Events Management</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Conference On Brain, Learning, Thinking, Creativity &amp; Memory</li>\r\n	<li>Mind Sports Championships &amp; Certification</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'services', '', '', '2012-04-22 12:20:08', '2012-04-22 04:20:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ideaspark/?page_id=15', 3, 'page', '', 0),
